'Cardamine bulbosa' is a species of flowering plant in the family Brassicaceae.
It is also commonly known as spring cress or bulbous bittercress.
The plant's leaves are compound with small leaflets, and its flowers are white with four petals.
The stems and leaves are green, and the plant can grow up to 30 cm tall.
Its seeds are produced in elongated pods that turn upwards as they mature.
'Cardamine bulbosa' is found in woodland areas and along streams throughout eastern North America.
It typically blooms in early spring, making it an important early-season food source for native insects.
